17:23.290 --> 17:24.660
ADRIANA:
Thank you.

17:24.880 --> 17:27.460
And now I'm going
to powder my nose.

17:27.460 --> 17:29.970
That was great, the way you
moved and danced...

17:29.970 --> 17:32.470
Rich, I've got to talk
to you a second, okay?

17:32.470 --> 17:35.470
What?
Uh...

17:35.470 --> 17:37.260
Adriana's married.

17:39.010 --> 17:40.810
Did you fall off
your bicycle again?

17:42.640 --> 17:44.650
Yeah, but that has
nothing to do with it.

17:44.650 --> 17:47.430
My father sends all her
bills to a Mr. Prescott.

17:48.680 --> 17:50.440
Oh.

17:50.650 --> 17:52.740
Well, just don't say
anything to anybody.

17:52.740 --> 17:54.740
Okay.

17:59.240 --> 18:00.250
Hi, Fonz.

18:00.250 --> 18:01.750
Hey, she was
pretty good, huh?

18:01.750 --> 18:04.250
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, didn't I tell you?

18:04.250 --> 18:06.120
S-she's something else.

18:06.420 --> 18:11.010
Fonz, uh, while we're
on the subject of Adriana,

18:11.010 --> 18:14.510
uh... did you know that...

18:15.010 --> 18:16.300
there's a Mr. Prescott?

18:16.460 --> 18:17.550
Oh, there's probably several.

18:17.550 --> 18:19.470
She comes
from a very large family.

18:20.930 --> 18:23.440
Well, uh, this Mr. Prescott...

18:23.440 --> 18:24.890
pays her gas bills.

18:25.270 --> 18:26.360
Could be her father.

18:26.360 --> 18:27.690
Could be her husband.

18:27.690 --> 18:29.270
Hey, hey--
let me ask you a question.

18:29.270 --> 18:30.780
Did you ever see
a ring on her finger?
No.

18:30.780 --> 18:32.060
All right,
what does that mean to you?

18:32.280 --> 18:35.360
She, uh...

18:35.360 --> 18:36.320
She lost it?

18:36.700 --> 18:37.570
Wrong.

18:39.150 --> 18:40.200
It means she ain't married.

18:40.570 --> 18:42.570
Okay, Fonz, if you say so.

18:42.910 --> 18:44.490
That's right, I say so.

18:45.990 --> 18:47.490
Hi.
Hi.

18:47.490 --> 18:50.460
That was really good,
the way you danced.

18:50.460 --> 18:52.000
Thank you.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.000
I'm going to get back
to the band.

18:55.500 --> 18:56.500
Yeah, you better do that.

18:59.000 --> 19:00.010
Want to dance?

19:00.510 --> 19:03.010
No, I feel like
sitting here and talking

19:03.010 --> 19:04.010
for just a minute,
all right?

19:04.010 --> 19:05.010
Okay.
Yeah.

19:05.510 --> 19:07.010
What do you want
to talk about?

19:07.010 --> 19:10.020
Well, let's start
with Mr. Prescott.

19:10.020 --> 19:11.850
What would you
like to know?

19:12.100 --> 19:13.990
I'd like to know
if he's your father.

19:14.190 --> 19:16.520
No, Mr. Prescott
is my husband.

19:16.740 --> 19:19.830
Well, then, I'd like to know
if he is your late husband.

19:22.330 --> 19:24.250
No, Mr. Prescott
is very much alive.

19:26.170 --> 19:27.670
Well, then I'd like to know

19:27.670 --> 19:29.620
if he is your
divorced husband.

19:29.950 --> 19:31.450
No.

19:33.460 --> 19:35.960
This is my last shot.

19:37.960 --> 19:39.380
Separated?

19:39.760 --> 19:41.210
Yes.

19:41.460 --> 19:42.550
Yeah.
(chuckles)

19:44.050 --> 19:45.020
I'll tell you something.

19:45.020 --> 19:47.050
You had me going there
for a minute, you know?

19:48.550 --> 19:51.060
Well, my husband
is 4,000 miles away

19:51.060 --> 19:53.560
trying to buy some
oil field or something.

19:53.560 --> 19:56.060
You see, Fonzie,
we have, um...

19:56.060 --> 19:57.560
we have an understanding.

19:57.560 --> 19:59.060
He doesn't tell
and I don't tell.

19:59.570 --> 20:00.570
I call that separated,
wouldn't you?

20:00.980 --> 20:03.370
Whoa, I call that apart.

20:05.150 --> 20:06.150
Well, don't let it bother you.

20:06.660 --> 20:07.410
You're making too much
out of it.

20:07.620 --> 20:09.710
Hey, let me tell you something.

20:09.710 --> 20:11.630
You know, I really like you.

20:11.960 --> 20:13.050
I mean, you're different

20:13.550 --> 20:14.410
from any woman
I've ever known.

20:14.710 --> 20:17.300
For one, you don't giggle.

20:17.300 --> 20:19.300
But, uh...

20:19.300 --> 20:22.300
I got some rules that I live by,
you understand?

20:22.300 --> 20:25.810
And one of them is that I don't
take what ain't mine,

20:25.810 --> 20:27.680
especially wives.

20:29.060 --> 20:30.060
You're serious?

20:30.430 --> 20:31.760
Oh, yeah, I'm serious.

20:31.980 --> 20:34.570
I'd like to talk about it.

20:34.930 --> 20:37.520
I don't see anything
to talk about.

20:37.520 --> 20:39.490
And dig it:
I ain't judging you.

20:39.490 --> 20:41.020
You understand?

20:41.020 --> 20:44.030
But I got my rules, and that's
the way I live my life.

20:44.440 --> 20:48.530
Well, I understand that, and I
also had a similar set of rules,

20:48.530 --> 20:51.450
but as I got older,
I sort of bent them a little.

20:51.830 --> 20:53.250
Whatever.

20:55.120 --> 20:56.960
Why didn't you tell me
that you were married?

20:57.170 --> 20:58.510
You didn't ask.

20:58.710 --> 21:00.290
All right, I didn't ask.

21:01.880 --> 21:03.380
Is that all that's
bothering you?

21:05.960 --> 21:08.050
Fonzie, I...

21:08.050 --> 21:09.550
I think I'm a little different,

21:09.550 --> 21:11.390
and I thought you
were a little different, too.

21:11.690 --> 21:13.610
That's why I never

21:13.860 --> 21:14.860
thought it mattered.

21:15.220 --> 21:16.780
It matters.

21:17.140 --> 21:18.690
I can see that.

21:20.610 --> 21:22.980
I'm sorry,
because I really like you.

21:24.320 --> 21:25.230
I like you, too.

21:28.650 --> 21:30.460
Uh...

21:32.740 --> 21:35.330
I'll just see
myself out.

21:38.330 --> 21:39.330
You're an interesting man.

21:39.330 --> 21:41.330
Yeah?
Yeah.

21:43.340 --> 21:45.840
Promise me you'll
still fix my car?

21:45.840 --> 21:48.340
Oh, yeah, as long
as Aunt Grace picks it up.

21:53.350 --> 21:54.850
I'm glad we met.

21:54.850 --> 21:56.850
I'm very glad we met, too.

